      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:7:16:12",
      "text": [
        " لَا يُجْزِئُ إِطْعَامُ الصَّغِيرِ فِي كَفَّارَةِ الْيَمِينِ وَ لَكِنْ صَغِيرَيْنِ بِكَبِيرٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Gayas Bin Ibrahim, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘It is not sufficient, feeding the young with regards to an expiation of the oath, but two young and an old one’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "12. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Muhammad ibn Yahya from Ghiyath ibn Ibrahim who has narrated the following: “Abu ‘ Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said in paying expiation for an oath, feeding small people is not sufficient, however, two small ones are equal to one grown-up person.”’ "
        ]
      }
